{ This line has become quite critical in recent years. White's idea is to delay the development of the light-squared bishop so that in the event of ...dxc4, Bxc4 would win a tempo. Furthermore, White makes sure that a recapture with the bishop on c3 is always possible, so quite often a3 will be played, as ...Bxc3 has now somewhat lost its appeal. Additionally, White clears the c1-square for the rook. }
