10. Bb5 h4 11. Be5 O-O
{ At first sight, it might look a bit odd to castle kingside since we have advanced both our h- and g-pawns. However, this move does enable the move ...Nxe5, and if White castles on the kingside in the future, we could use our pawns to launch an initiative on that side of the board. }
12. h3 { White's most testing move. } 12... Nxe5
{ Objectively, there is nothing wrong with  12...Ne4  .  However, the lines get extremely sharp, and one wrong move could lead to a very bad position for Black. }
13. dxe5 Ne4 14. Bd3
{ 14.Nf3  c6  15.Bd3  f5  transposes to the line at hand. } 14... f5 15. a3
{ The only critical move. } 15... Bxc3+ 16. bxc3 Bd7
