{ The most accurate follow-up. We develop the knight and keep our options open for our other pieces. }
12. a3 Bxc3
{ It might seem like a concession to give up the bishop pair, but in return, Black will get excellent play on the light squares. Furthermore, White’s bishop on d2 will struggle to play a meaningful role here. }
13. bxc3 Na5
{ We will follow up with ...Nb3. Black has good play to compensate for White's bishop pair. }
