Na6
{ Threatening ...Nb4, which would win the bishop pair, and now  12.Nb5  can be comfortably met with  12...Bf8  . }
12. a3
{ As mentioned,  12.Nb5  is just a storm in a teapot since Black can simply retreat the bishop with  12...Bf8  and follow up with the ...c5 plan. }
12... c5
{ Black has plenty of active play and the position is dynamically balanced. For example,  13.e4  only looks aggressive but in reality, it is harmless. Following  13...cxd4  14.Nxd5  Rc8  15.Nxf6+  Qxf6  ,  we are very comfortable, and ...Nc5 will come next. }
