13... Bxc3
{ By trading on c3 first, we make sure that we do not have to recapture in the event of Nxc6.  13...Qd6  is possible as well, but the text is easier. }
14. bxc3 fxe6 15. Nxc6 Qe8
{ Escaping the threat of the knight and defending the pawn on e6. White has to move the knight now. }
16. Ne5 Ne4
{ This is the point behind our play, as we now have a double attack on the f2 and c3-pawns. }
17. Rf1
{ White's only move to maintain the balance since now ...Nxc3 will not fork the queen and rook anymore. }
17... Nxc3
{ We have regained the pawn and have nothing to worry about here due to our active pieces. The knight will often return to d5, and we can further improve our position with ...Rc8. }
