14... Bxc3 { We should remove the knight before taking on d5. } 15. bxc3 Bxd5
{ We can avoid an immediate draw by taking the pawn with  15...exd5  . However, White will have strong compensation after  16.Bd3  followed by Qh5, as our king will be quite weak. }
16. Qg4+ Kh8 17. Qh4
{ White's best move, but this leads to nothing more than a repetition.  17.Qf4  Bxc4  18.Qxf6+  leads to the same thing. }
17... Bxc4 18. Qxf6+ Kg8 19. Qg5+ Kh8 20. Qf6+ Kg8
{ And we can sign the scoresheets. } *

