{ There are other moves as well, but I like this one due to its simplicity. Our idea is to play ...h6, so that we can meet Bh4 with ...Nf4, forking the queen on e2 and the g2-pawn. }
15. f3
{ With this move, White makes sure that the g2-pawn will not be hanging, so ...h6 can now be met with Bh4. However, it does slightly weaken White's position. }
15... Rac8
{ Black has a fine game, as we have the better pawn structure and our pieces are nicely coordinated. A good plan here would be to go ...N7f6-h5-f4. }
