9. Nxc3
{ This allows us to give White an isolated pawn on d4, and we definitely should, as the weak pawn on d4 will compensate for White having the bishop pair.   9.bxc3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/pppp1ppp/4pn2/8/1bPP4/2N5/PP2PPPP/R1BQKBNR w KQkq - 2 4@@EndFEN@@  4.e3  O-O  5.Bd3  d5  6.a3  . }
9... cxd4 10. Qxd4
{ This was played by my good friend Erwin l’Ami in the recent Tata Steel Challengers. }
10... Qxd4
{ We should certainly trade queens, as it gives White the isolated pawn on d4. }
11. exd4 Rd8
{ Attacking the pawn on d4 and making sure that White cannot get rid of the isolani with d5. }
12. Be3 { Developing the bishop and defending the pawn on d4. } 12... b6
{ Black had a fine game here in L'Ami-Sindarov, Wijk aan Zee 2023, as White’s isolated pawn on d4 compensates for White having the bishop pair. Next, we can continue with ...Ba6 and ...Nc6-e7, to firmly block a potential d5 break. }
