19. Bxh7+ Kxh7 20. Qh5+ Kg8 21. Bxg7 Kxg7 22. Qg5+ Kh7
{ After  23.Qh4+  Kg8  24.Qg5+  Kh7  , a draw is imminent.  It would be risky for White to play for more here. }
23. f5 f6 24. Qxe3 Bd5
{ White certainly has compensation for the piece, but with ...Ne5 to follow, I do not see how White is breaking through. }
