{ This is somewhat risky for White, as we are just going to grab a pawn. } 5...
dxc4 { We will not give this pawn back easily. } 6. e3 b5
{ Hanging on to the pawn. } 7. a4 c6
{ Black's position is already preferable. Next up, we are going to play ...Bb7, ...Nbd7, and ...a6 if needed, and I do not see how White is getting the pawn back. }
