14. e3 Bf5
{ 14...Bg4  is also possible. This leads to more forcing variations. I prefer  14...Bf5  , as it leaves more play in the position and Black has the potential to outplay White, which is what happened in the game between Hans Niemann and Fabiano Caruana at the 2022 US Championship. }
15. Qxc7
{ This move has not been played in any games, and understandably so. For the sacrificed pawn, Black gets a strong initiative that should guarantee us equality. }
15... Nd7 16. Qxb7 Rab8 17. Qc6 Rxb2
{ Black has full compensation for the pawn due to the active pieces. Furthermore, White is still struggling to complete development. }
