{ Pinning the pawn on e3 and thus threatening ...Nxd4.  10...h4  11.Be5  Qe7  will probably lead to the same variations, but I prefer  @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/ppp2p2/2n2n2/3p2pp/1b1P4/2NBP1B1/PPQ2PPP/R3K1NR b KQkq - 1 10@@EndFEN@@  10...Qe7  as it gives White less options. }
