5... c5 { We should exert pressure on White's center as quickly as possible. }
6. d5
{ 6.Qb3  transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/pppp1ppp/4pn2/8/1bPP4/2N2N2/PP2PPPP/R1BQKB1R w KQ - 4 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Qb3  c5  6.Bg5  . }
6... h6 { It is always useful to include this move. } 7. Bh4 exd5 8. cxd5 d6 9.
e3 Nbd7 10. Bd3 Qb6
{ The idea behind this move is to unpin the queen so we can take on c3 and on d5. Furthermore, the queen is slightly better placed on b6 than a5, as it will help defend the pawn on d6. }
11. O-O Bxc3 12. bxc3 Nxd5
{ We are up a pawn and the onus is on White to prove the compensation. We will often play ...N5f6, and it is not easy at all for White to get the pawn back. }
