{ Pushing White’s knight back and continuing our initiative in the center. }
10. Nf3 d4
{ The best way to deal with White's pressure on our center. We can use our lead in development to open the position and activate our pieces quickly. }
11. exd4 exd4 12. Qxd4
{ The best way for White to take the pawn. Black gets a strong initiative after  12.Nxd4  Qb6  with ...Rd8 coming next. }
12... Qe7+ 13. Qe3 Qxe3+ 14. fxe3 Ne4
{ White will soon be left with a bunch of weaknesses. Black is already for choice. }
