10. Nge2
{ This is how the game Shlyakhtenko-Burke, Philadelphia 2022 continued. Here I suggest the following improvement: }
10... Nbd7
{ The game continued  10...O-O  11.Ng3  h5  12.Be2  h4  13.Nf1  Nbd7  .  Here,  14.g4Ν  would have been a strong improvement. The position is quite messy but things can become quite dangerous, as White will play Ne3 and O-O next and will just start storming on the kingside. }
11. Ng3 h5 12. Nf5 Nb6 { Protecting a4, d6, and challenging the knight on f5. }
13. Ne3
{ Taking on g7 is not a good idea, as after  13.Nxg7+?  Kf8  14.Nf5  Bxf5  ,  White's center collapses:  15.exf5  Nfxd5-+  . }
13... Nfd7 14. Be2 Qh4+
{ By provoking g3, we make White's kingside pawn structure slightly looser and White's king will be slightly more exposed. Furthermore, we will have ...Bh3 in many lines. }
15. g3 Qf6 16. O-O O-O
{ We will play ...Ne5 in the foreseeable future and we will have the type of fighting game we are looking for in this repertoire. I would pick Black here. }
