[White "10) Nimzo-Indian − Sidelines"]
[Black "Spielmann Variation 4.Qb3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qb3
{ The Spielmann Variation of the Nimzo. White's idea is to attack our bishop on b4 and simultaneously enable themselves to recapture with the queen on c3 to keep the pawn structure intact. However, the drawback is that the queen is somewhat misplaced on b3, compared to, say, c2. }
4... c5
{ Defending the bishop on b4 and putting pressure on White's center right away. }
5. a3
{ With this move, White grabs the bishop pair, but in exchange, we get a big lead in development. }
5... Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 cxd4 7. Qxd4 Nc6
{ We will follow up with ...O-O and ...d5 and White needs to be careful, as our initiative can become quite powerful. }
*

