[White "12) 1.d4 Nf6 2.Nc3"]
[Black "Jobava London 3.Bf4 c5 4.e3 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nc3
{ By playing Nc3, White prepares the move 3.e4. As we don't want to give White the full center, we have to play ...d5. }
2... d5
{ Structurally speaking, White's knight is misplaced on c3. It stops White from exerting pressure on Black's center with c2-c4, and it also prevents White from strengthening their own center with c2-c3. However, White usually plays for quick development in this opening. }
3. Bf4
{ The Jobava London. This has become a popular weapon in rapid and blitz games, as White has quick development and many traps. However, with accurate play, Black gets a good game. }
3... c5
{ Challenging White’s center right away. I like this move, as it is the most direct. }
4. e3
{ The calmer approach. White intends to recapture on d4 with the e-pawn and play a Carlsbad structure. }
4... cxd4 5. exd4 a6
{ Stopping Nb5. Structurally speaking, Black is doing very well, as White's knight is misplaced on c3. White has to try to do something quickly, as otherwise, they are just worse if we get ...Nc6 and ...Bg4/f5 in. }
6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Ne5
{ The only critical move. After any other move, we develop our bishop to g4 or f5 and get a very comfortable position. White further activates the knight and also creates the positional threat of Nxc6, as ...bxc6 would be slightly detrimental to our pawn structure. }
7... Bd7
{ Therefore, we play this move so we can recapture with the bishop on c6 and keep our pawn structure intact. Again, if White were to play slowly here, Black is completely fine. So every top game from this position continued with g4. }
8. Be2 e6 9. O-O Qb6
{ This move is quite effective, as we attack both pawns on d4 and b2. } 10.
Nxc6
{ White has to trade, to eliminate the threat on the d4-pawn. However, this is quite toothless, as White exchanges their most active piece. }
10... Bxc6 11. Rb1 { Defending the b2-pawn. } 11... Be7
{ Black has a comfortable game here, as the knight is misplaced on c3 in this structure. Next up, we are going to castle. }
*

