1. d4 Nf6
{ In this chapter, we will be looking at all of the sidelines White can try starting from the second and third moves. Note that lines with an early Nf3 will not be covered in this course, as those will be addressed in part 2 of my Lifetime Repertoire, which will be centered around the Queen's Indian.  Against most of White's sidelines, we will play ...d5 as placing a pawn in the center is rarely a bad idea, and after that, we will often either play ...Bf5 or ...c5. }
