[Black "1.d4 Nf6 2.e3 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. e3
{ Since White is delaying the move Nf3, they can opt to play a Stonewall system. The most important thing against Stonewall setups will be to develop our light-squared bishop, ideally to f5, but g4 is also not a bad square. }
2... d5 3. f4 Bf5
{ White's Stonewall setup is clearly bound to fail, as we have managed to develop our bishop and therefore have firm control over the e4-square. Next up, we are going to play ...e6, ...c5, and ...Nc6. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
